model.name: MirhakkakSchaeuble2021 - a Candida albicans genome-scale metabolic model reconstruction

body.p: A genome-scale metabolic model (GEM) of C. albicans was reconstructed and curated by using phenotypic microarray data and resolving erroneous energy-generating cycles. It comprises 771 genes, 3082 metabolic reactions and 2733 metabolites. In Mirhakkak et al. 2021 (https://doi.org/10.1038/s41396-020-00848-z) the C. albicans GEM was simulated together with bacterial GEMs to assess key determinants of C. albicans gut colonization levels.
